---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Beginning with PRE — Plan Ahead for Scrabble Success"
  description="Master PRE- prefix words in Scrabble with high-scoring examples, front-hooking plays, and bingo potential. The 'before' prefix that sets up winning moves."
  keywords="scrabble words starting with pre, pre prefix scrabble, words beginning with pre, pre words strategy, front hooking pre, high scoring pre words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Beginning with PRE — Plan Ahead for Scrabble Success",
    "description": "Master PRE- prefix words in Scrabble with high-scoring examples, front-hooking plays, and bingo potential. The 'before' prefix that sets up winning moves.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-beginning-with-pre" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the highest scoring Scrabble words beginning with PRE?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "PREMIX (17 pts), PRETEXT (16 pts), and PREVIEW (15 pts) are among the highest-scoring playable PRE- words. The 3-tile prefix (P=3, R=1, E=1 for 5 points) is worth the investment when paired with high-value roots like MIX, TEXT, and VIEW." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I front-hook PRE onto words already on the Scrabble board?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — PRE- front-hooks onto many words already on the board. If HEAT is played, extend to PREHEAT. If PAID is there, make it PREPAID. If VIEW is on the board, play PREVIEW. The 3-tile investment (P=3, R=1, E=1 = 5 pts) scores the full extended word, often reaching premium squares." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does PRE- help with bingos in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "PRE- uses 3 of your 7 tiles, leaving you needing only a 4-letter root for a bingo. This makes it slightly harder than 2-letter prefixes but still very achievable. Common PRE- bingos include PREVENT, PRETEND, PRECISE, PREMIUM, and PREPARE — all using frequently drawn tiles." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Beginning with PRE — Plan Ahead for Scrabble Success</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        The PRE- prefix means "before" and attaches to hundreds of English words to create valid Scrabble plays. At 3 tiles (P=3, R=1, E=1 for 5 points), it's a slightly heavier investment than UN- or RE-, but the payoff is significant — PRE- words tend to be longer, hit premium squares more reliably, and produce some of the game's most satisfying front-hooks when you extend words already on the board.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring PRE- Words for Scrabble</h2>

      <p>These PRE- words deliver strong scores by combining the 3-letter prefix with high-value roots. The P tile's 3-point value means even short PRE- words carry decent base scores.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREMIX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To mix in advance</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PRETEXT</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A false excuse</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREVIEW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Advance showing</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREWASH</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To wash beforehand</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREVAIL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To triumph over</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREVENT</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To stop from happening</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREHEAT</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To heat beforehand</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREPAID</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Paid in advance</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PRECISE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Exactly defined</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREMIUM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Superior quality</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PREPARE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To make ready</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PRETEND</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To make believe</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PRESIDE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To lead or chair</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PRE- prefix cost</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1,200+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid PRE- words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 letters</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Root needed for bingo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Front-Hooking with PRE — Extend Board Words</h2>

      <p>PRE- front-hooks create some of the most dramatic score swings in Scrabble. Adding 3 tiles to the front of an existing word scores the entire extended word — and the longer the base word, the bigger your payoff.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 PRE- Extension Strategy</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">When your opponent plays <span class="text-white font-medium">HEAT</span>, you score for <span class="text-white font-medium">PREHEAT</span> (12 pts). When <span class="text-white font-medium">VIEW</span> is on the board, play <span class="text-white font-medium">PREVIEW</span> (15 pts). The 3-tile prefix turns a modest opponent word into your premium play — especially powerful when the extension reaches a Triple Word Score.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HEAT → PREHEAT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">VIEW → PREVIEW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">PAID → PREPAID</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SET → PRESET</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">TEND → PRETEND</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">WASH → PREWASH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15 pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">PRE- Bingo Potential — 3 + 4 = 7</h2>

      <p>PRE- consumes 3 tiles, meaning you need only a 4-letter root to form a 7-letter bingo. While this leaves less room than UN- or RE-, there are still hundreds of viable 4-letter roots that combine with PRE- for bingos.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">PRE + 4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letters needed for bingo</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~8%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Of bingos use PRE-</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">60+ pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Typical PRE- bingo score</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Strong PRE- bingo roots to memorize: VENT (PREVENT), TEND (PRETEND), PARE (PREPARE), SIDE (PRESIDE), VAIL (PREVAIL), MIUM (PREMIUM), and CISE (PRECISE). Keep these 4-letter combinations in mind when you draw P, R, E together.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy — Managing the P Tile</h2>

      <p>The P tile (3 points) is the anchor of the PRE- prefix. Deciding whether to hold it alongside R and E or play it independently is a critical rack management choice.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold P+R+E when:</span> Your remaining 4 tiles form a recognizable root (VENT, TEND, PARE, HEAT, VIEW). Three tiles is a bigger commitment than 2-tile prefixes, so only hold when you can see a clear bingo path within 1-2 turns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play P separately when:</span> Your rack lacks vowel balance or you have duplicate consonants. P scores well in short words (PAX, POX, PEW) and on Double/Triple Letter Squares. Don't sacrifice immediate scoring for a speculative PRE- play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target existing words:</span> PRE- front-hooks are especially strong because the 3-letter extension covers more board squares. If HEAT sits 3 squares from a Triple Word Score, your PREHEAT hits it perfectly — scoring triple the entire 12-point word.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Combine prefixes mentally:</span> PRE- + back-hooks create 8-letter bingos through board tiles. PREVENT + ED = PREVENTED, PREPARE + D = PREPARED. If you can use a tile already on the board as part of your word, the bingo becomes easier to achieve.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Summary</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Summary</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The PRE- prefix is your <span class="text-white font-medium">planning-ahead play</span> in Scrabble. With 1,200+ valid words, strong front-hooking potential on common board words, and accessible bingo paths (PRE + 4 letters), it rewards players who think one turn ahead. Hold P, R, E when a clear root exists in your remaining tiles, always scan for hookable words like HEAT, VIEW, and PAID, and remember that the 5-point prefix investment regularly generates 50+ point bingo returns.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/bingo-stem-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Bingo Stem Strategy — Building 7-Letter Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-in-tion/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending in TION — Score Big with Latin Roots</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-in-able/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending in ABLE — Flexible Suffix Mastery</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find PRE- words from your rack tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
